<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The assignment response[idx_response] = '\0'; writes a terminating NUL into the buffer that is never used: the function later sends response with length idx_response (excluding the terminator) and then frees the buffer. No string functions read the terminator and no other code relies on it, so removing this assignment would not change program behaviour. Therefore this executed assignment is dead code (violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2).
